{
  "texts": [
    "3.14 Agents score their subscriptions to monitor the interest they have in maintaining them.",
    "For every subscription s ji of i to j, the disagreement δ ij (t) ≥ 0 of i with the content received through s ji is initialized at 0 and updated at each time step according to",
    ", with γ < 1 being a daily discount factor and n t ij the number of messages read by i during time step t that have been authored or relayed by j.",
    "If s ji (t) = 1 and the disagreement δ ij (t) > τ, i will unsubscribe from j, i.e., s ji (t + 1) = 0.",
    "3.15 1/γ is a characteristic time of agents' evolution that is difficult to estimate empirically."
  ]
}